    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-07T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-07T21:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/112: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-08T12:00:00+10:00"
                            >January 8, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 8—2:29
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s telegram of June 13, 3 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d10fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1934v01#pg_842">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 842</ref>.</note> Under instructions of
                    Prime Minister now attending Cabinet meeting in Melbourne, his Secretary today
                    telephoned from Canberra inquiring whether I had received the Department’s reply
                    to the Australian trade proposal and requested me to ascertain for telegraphic
                    information as to probable date of receipt which he hoped might be in the very
                    near future as Cabinet is now considering such matters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
